        "The matrix $Q^*Q$ should be the identity, up to roundoff error.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Proposition 11.6: Projection formula\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-important}\n",
        "Let $u_1,\\ldots,u_k$ be an orthonormal basis for a subspace $W$ of a complex inner product space. Then\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\operatorname{proj}_W(y)=\\sum_{i=1}^k \\langle y,u_i\\rangle u_i.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "In matrix form, if\n",
        "$$\n",
        "U=[u_1\\ \\cdots\\ u_k],\n",
        "$$\n",
        "then\n",
        "$$\n",
        "P_W=UU^*.\n",
        "$$\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "<details>\n",
        "<summary><strong>Show proof</strong></summary>\n",
        "\n",
        "Let\n",
        "$$\n",
        "p=\\sum_{i=1}^k\\langle y,u_i\\rangle u_i.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "For each $j$,\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\langle y-p,u_j\\rangle\n",
        "=\\langle y,u_j\\rangle-\n",
        "\\sum_{i=1}^k\\langle y,u_i\\rangle\\langle u_i,u_j\\rangle\n",
        "=0.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Thus $y-p$ is orthogonal to every vector in $W$. Therefore $p$ is the orthogonal projection of $y$ onto $W$.\n",
        "\n",
        "</details>"
      ],
