        "## Conjugate transpose, adjoints, and unitary matrices\n",
        "\n",
        "### Definition 11.7: Conjugate transpose\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "For a complex matrix $A=(a_{ij})\\in\\mathbb C^{m\\times n}$, the **conjugate transpose** is\n",
        "$$\n",
        "A^*=\\overline{A}^{T}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Equivalently,\n",
        "$$\n",
        "(A^*)_{ij}=\\overline{a_{ji}}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "### Definition 11.8: Adjoint\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "Let $T:V\\to V$ be a linear transformation on a finite-dimensional complex inner product space. The **adjoint** of $T$ is the unique linear map $T^*:V\\to V$ satisfying\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\langle T u,v\\rangle=\\langle u,T^*v\\rangle\n",
        "$$\n",
        "for all $u,v\\in V$.\n",
        "With respect to an orthonormal basis, the matrix of $T^*$ is the conjugate transpose of the matrix of $T$.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "### Definition 11.9: Unitary matrix\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "A square matrix $U\\in\\mathbb C^{n\\times n}$ is **unitary** if\n",
        "$$\n",
        "U^*U=UU^*=I.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Equivalently, the columns of $U$ form an orthonormal basis of $\\mathbb C^n$.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "### Proposition 11.10: Unitary matrices preserve geometry\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-important}\n",
        "If $U$ is unitary, then for all $x,y\\in\\mathbb C^n$,\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\langle Ux,Uy\\rangle=\\langle x,y\\rangle.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "In particular,\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\|Ux\\|=\\|x\\|.\n",
        "$$\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "<details>\n",
        "<summary><strong>Show proof</strong></summary>\n",
        "\n",
        "Using $\\langle x,y\\rangle=y^*x$,\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\langle Ux,Uy\\rangle=(Uy)^*(Ux)=y^*U^*Ux=y^*x=\\langle x,y\\rangle.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "Setting $x=y$ gives preservation of norm.\n",
        "\n",
        "</details>"
      ],
      "id": "feb1a3c8"
    },
